race.comment: BALMIERRO (2) found the lead a long way out and was claimed late last start over 1900m at Armidale. Has a win on the CV over 2200m. Rock hard fit after four runs back from a spell and this step up in trip comes at the perfect time. CRIMSON SPIRIT (7) rallied late to get up for third recently over 1800m at the Gold Coast. Fitter for three runs back from a spell and is looking for this journey now. Expect the winner to come from this pair. WOODLAND WONDER (6) is dour and can sneak into the frame while PURPLE KITTY (9) is new to the staying trip but should give backers a sight. The lightly raced AYASAKI (1) is fitter for two runs back from a spell and did win here last prep.
